    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 18 is anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18), both of whom benefit from exceptional matchup conditions. **Kyle Tucker** draws a prime assignment against Feltner, pairing a 14% park factor boost with a robust 8% lineup order adjustment to solidify his status as our primary producer. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** leads off with a massive 10% order bonus and a favorable matchup against Williams; while we accounted for a slight negative drag due to the pitcher\u2019s elite hold efficiency, **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start given his capacity to impact all five categories. **Andy Pages** (75.63) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) round out our top-tier tier of plays, with both capitalizing on exploitable SP_xERA profiles and favorable platoon splits.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the exclusion of **Nasim Nunez** (60.21), who posted a strong score but ultimately yielded to the depth of our outfield and middle infield rotations. While **Nasim Nunez** offers valuable speed, the combination of a lower order slot and an aggressive opposing catcher pop time resulted in a slight efficiency dip compared to **Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Jacob Wilson** (70.28). **Josh Lowe** in particular remains a high-variance, high-reward play today; despite hitting lower in the order, his efficiency is buoyed by a significant park factor and a slow opposing delivery that screams stolen base potential. We are monitoring the weather closely across all venues, though no immediate risks have necessitated a tactical shift from our projected lineup. **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.07) represents our lowest-scoring starter, and while his platoon split against Taillon is less than ideal, his raw talent keeps him above the benching threshold for today\u2019s contest.",
